=== Etymology ===
From the Old English ''[[anderne]]'' (''[[aunderne]]'', ''[[aundyre]]''), from the Old French ''[[andier]]'', from the French ''[[landier]]'', From the Late Latin ''[[andena]]'', (''[[andela]]'', ''[[anderia]]'').
===Noun===
'''andiron''' (''plural'' andirons)
#A utensil for supporting wood when burning in a [[fireplace]], one being placed on each side; a [[firedog]]; as, a pair of andirons.
